issue.title: remove identity in transformers model graph fusion

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

PyTorch v1.12 export model has Identity nodes even with constant folding enabled in torch.onnx.export. Those Identity nodes causes problem in transformers graph fusion because some fusion expects input to be initializer.

Add a preprocessing to remove those Identity nodes.

Also add symbolic shape inference function for Identity operator.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

It is a workaround for https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12192. After this change, the optimized gpt-2 fp32 model can run symbolic shape inference, and no more infinite loop. It did not fix the root cause or infinite loop bug in symbolic shape inference.

This fixes https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12199, https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12154

issue.title: Improve symbolic shape inference in transformers tools

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

Improve symbolic shape inference using in tranformers tools:
(1) Use max_runs=128 (shall be enough for most models) to avoid infinite loop.
(2) Remove duplicated key "Gelu" in symbolic_shape_infer.py
(3) Disable symbolic shape inference when it failed to suppress similar error message.
(4) Update fusion_skiplayernorm.py to show warning of shape inference failure only once.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

Walkaround for https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12192.
